(616, 'Florence Foster Jenkins (2016)', '2017/07/film-florence-foster-jenkins-2016.jpg', '', 'bkJNVVN4NzJFZ2VFK3pmL3JHTUJqOUpCb2hRWklZZ3lQUnhoNmUxREdWZz0=', '&lt;p&gt;Florence Foster Jenkins, an heiress form NYC always wanted to be a concert pianist and play Carnegie Hall. An injury in her youth deterred that dream. So she sets out to sing her way to Carnegie Hall knowing the only way to get there would be &amp;#8220;Practice Practice Practice&amp;#8221;. Her husband supports her venture and the true story of Florence Foster Jenkins playing Carnegie Hall becomes a truly historic event.&lt;br /&gt;Stephen Frears&lt;br /&gt;Meryl Streep, Hugh Grant, Simon Helberg, Rebecca Ferguson&lt;br /&gt;29 Mar 2016 (UK)&lt;br /&gt;Nominated for 4 Golden Globes. Another 3 wins &amp;#038; 17 nominations.&lt;br /&gt;', 'Biography', 'Biography, Comedy, Drama', 'Stephen Frears', 'Hugh Grant, Meryl Streep, Rebecca Ferguson, Simon Helberg', 'Uk', 'BluRay', '6.9', '1 jam 50 menit', '2016-03-29'),
(617, 'Fences (2016)', '2017/07/film-fences-2016.jpg', '', 'aXR6MnlLV0FvVXd2UTNSaTF2NkRUZlF2dXQxdU1LTWVoQ0p4ZlVlcTR1az0=', '&lt;p&gt;Troy Maxson makes his living as a sanitation worker in 1950s Pittsburgh. Maxson once dreamed of becoming a professional baseball player, but was deemed too old when the major leagues began admitting black athletes. Bitter over his missed opportunity, Troy creates further tension in his family when he squashes his son&amp;#8217;s chance to meet a college football recruiter.&lt;br /&gt;Denzel Washington&lt;br /&gt;Denzel Washington, Viola Davis, Stephen Henderson, Jovan Adepo&lt;br /&gt;16 Dec 2016 (USA)&lt;br /&gt;Nominated for 4 Oscars. Another 39 wins &amp;#038; 92 nominations.&lt;br /&gt;', 'Father, Based On Play, Race Relations, Racism, African American, Pittsburgh, 1950s, Struggle', 'Drama', 'Denzel Washington', 'Denzel Washington, Jovan Adepo, Stephen Henderson, Viola Davis', 'Usa', 'BluRay', '7.3', '2 jam 19 menit', '2016-12-16'),
(618, 'Don&amp;#039;t Breathe (2016)', '2017/07/film-dont-breathe-2016.jpg', '', 'Z1puaW1yaURhcjg1OVYvTTdRRCtzSC96VDR5SzBZMm9MWTczK1paK2gzZz0=', '&lt;p&gt;Rocky, a young woman wanting to start a better life for her and her sister, agrees to take part in the robbery of a house owned by a wealthy blind man with her boyfriend Money and their friend Alex. But when the blind man turns out to be a serial killer, the group must find a way to escape his home before they become his newest victims.&lt;br /&gt;Fede Alvarez&lt;br /&gt;Jane Levy, Stephen Lang, Dylan Minnette, Jane May Graves&lt;br /&gt;25 Aug 2016 (USA)&lt;br /&gt;', 'Teenager, Blind, Break In, Blind Man', 'Horror, Thriller', 'Fede Alvarez', 'Dylan Minnette, Jane Levy, Jane May Graves, Stephen Lang', 'Usa', 'BluRay', '7.2', '1 jam 28 menit', '2016-08-25'),
(619, 'Ethel &amp;amp; Ernest (2016)', '2017/07/film-ethel-ernest-2016.jpg', '', 'SE9QV082R3RCSDRNZWtBSDBmQnVQZTgxcE4xdU5VMGt5NHlCV3MxMVJabz0=', '&lt;p&gt;In 1928 London milk-man Ernest Briggs courts and marries house-maid Ethel, their son Raymond being born in 1934. When World War II breaks out Ethel tearfully allows him to be evacuated to aunts in Dorset whilst Ernest joins the fire service, shocked by the carnage he sees. As hostilities end they celebrate Raymond&amp;#8217;s return and entry to grammar school and the birth of the welfare state though Ethel is mistrustful of socialism and progress in general. Raymond himself progresses from National Service to art college and a teaching post, worrying his mother by marrying schizophrenic Jean. However father and son console each other as Ethel slips away but before long Raymond is mourning his father too though both Ethel and Ernest will forever be immortalized by Raymond&amp;#8217;s touching account of their lives.&lt;br /&gt;Roger Mainwood&lt;br /&gt;Luke Treadaway, Jim Broadbent, Pam Ferris, Brenda Blethyn&lt;br /&gt;28 Oct 2016 (UK)&lt;br /&gt;', '', 'Animation, Drama, History', 'Roger Mainwood', 'Brenda Blethyn, Jim Broadbent, Luke Treadaway, Pam Ferris', 'Uk', 'HDRip', '7.9', '1 jam 34 menit', '2016-10-28'),
